<doc id="901389" wikidata="Q4857366" url="?curid=901389" title="Banyen Rakgan">
<text>Banyen Rakkaen (; ) (born on October 14, 1952, to an Isan family in Ubon Ratchathani province in the Isan region of Northeast Thailand) is a &quot;Thai mor lam&quot; and &quot;Thai luk thung&quot; singer. Banyen Rakkaen is known as the &quot;Queen of mor lam&quot; and after 45 years in the business she was named a National Artist in 2014 for her contribution to folk music.

== Biography ==
She is also a student of National Artist, Master Chaweewan Dumnern.

Banyen was the first national &quot;mor lam&quot; star, whose appearances on television in the 1980s brought the form to an audience beyond its northeastern heartland.
She bridges the gap between traditional and modern &quot;mor lam&quot;, normally appearing in traditional clothing but using electrified instruments and singing &quot;luk thung&quot; and dance-influenced songs.

