<doc id="901443" wikidata="Q4924109" url="?curid=901443" title="Siriporn Ampaipong">
<text>Siriporn Ampaipong (Alternative spelling: Siriporn Umpaipong; ; , birth name Sirima Amken; ; ; born Monday December 7, 1964) is a &quot;mor lam&quot; and &quot;luk thung&quot; singer from the Isan region of Thailand.

Siriporn Ampaipong was born into a family of &quot;mor lam&quot; singers in Udon Thani Province. Most of her songs are sentimental ballads. She has released eight hit albums between 2001 and 2004, and is regarded as one of Thailand&#x27;s most popular folk singers.

